   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Project 85 \\u2014 Local Image Captioning Notebook\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Generate captions for images using a local VLM \\u2014 fully offline.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Component | Choice |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|-----------|--------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| VLM | Ollama (llava or minicpm-v) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Fallback | Text-based simulation |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Interface | Jupyter |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> **Note:** This notebook uses Ollama\\u2019s VLM support. If no VLM is available,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> it falls back to a text-based simulation for learning purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 1 \\u00b7 What You Will Learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. How to use a **local VLM** for image captioning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. How to send **images to Ollama** via LangChain\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. How to create **synthetic image descriptions** as fallback\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. How to compare **caption quality** across prompts\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2 \\u00b7 Why It Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Image captioning powers accessibility, content moderation, search indexing,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and multimodal RAG \\u2014 all without sending data to external APIs.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3 \\u00b7 Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama Pillow\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 4 \\u00b7 Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import json, base64, io\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from pathlib import Path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Try VLM first, fall back to text-only\\n\",\n",
    "    \"VLM_MODEL = 'minicpm-v'  # or 'llava'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TEXT_MODEL = 'qwen3:8b'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    vlm = ChatOllama(model=VLM_MODEL, temperature=0.3)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    vlm.invoke('test')  # quick check\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    USE_VLM = True\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'VLM ready: {VLM_MODEL}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    USE_VLM = False\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    vlm = ChatOllama(model=TEXT_MODEL, temperature=0.3)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'VLM not available, using text fallback: {TEXT_MODEL}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 5 \\u00b7 Create Sample Images\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We create simple images with Pillow for testing. In production,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"you\\u2019d load real photos.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from PIL import Image, ImageDraw, ImageFont\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def create_test_image(text, filename, bg='white', fg='black'):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    img = Image.new('RGB', (400, 300), bg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    draw = ImageDraw.Draw(img)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    draw.text((20, 130), text, fill=fg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    img.save(filename)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return filename\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Path('sample_images').mkdir(exist_ok=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"images = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    create_test_image('Office Meeting\\\\n5 people around table', 'sample_images/meeting.png', '#e0e0ff'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    create_test_image('Product Dashboard\\\\nCharts and graphs', 'sample_images/dashboard.png', '#f0f0f0'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    create_test_image('Sunset over mountains\\\\nOrange sky, dark peaks', 'sample_images/sunset.png', '#ffcc80'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Created {len(images)} test images')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 6 \\u00b7 Generate Captions\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def caption_image(img_path, prompt='Describe this image in one sentence.'):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if USE_VLM:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        with open(img_path, 'rb') as f:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            b64 = base64.b64encode(f.read()).decode()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        msg = HumanMessage(content=[\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            {'type': 'text', 'text': prompt},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            {'type': 'image_url', 'image_url': f'data:image/png;base64,{b64}'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return vlm.invoke([msg]).content\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Text fallback: describe what the image filename suggests\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        name = Path(img_path).stem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        fallback_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            ('system', 'Imagine you are looking at an image. Generate a caption based on the description.'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            ('human', 'Image description hint: {hint}. Write a natural caption.'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return (fallback_prompt | vlm | StrOutputParser()).invoke({'hint': name.replace('_',' ')})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"captions = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for img in images:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cap = caption_image(img)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    captions.append({'image': img, 'caption': cap})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'{Path(img).name}: {cap[:100]}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 7 \\u00b7 Compare Prompt Styles\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"PROMPTS = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'Describe this image briefly.',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'What objects and people are in this image?',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'Write an alt-text description for accessibility.',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for img in images[:1]:  # Test on first image\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'\\\\nImage: {Path(img).name}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for p in PROMPTS:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        cap = caption_image(img, p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f'  [{p[:30]}...] {cap[:80]}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 8 \\u00b7 Export\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"with open('captions.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(captions, f, indent=2, default=str)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Saved.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 9 \\u00b7 Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Local VLMs (llava, minicpm-v) caption images without cloud APIs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Prompt style affects caption detail and focus\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Alt-text prompts produce accessibility-ready descriptions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Fallback to text simulation keeps the notebook runnable everywhere\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
